The African Transformation Movement is back in court today. They want it to force a secret ballot in a motion of no confidence in President Cyril Ramaphosa. The party says Ramaphosa failed to disclose to Parliament that he benefitted financially from his ANC presidential campaign in 2017. ATM has taken a jab at National Assembly Speaker Thandi Modise's decision to refuse a secret ballot claiming she's biased and irrational. eNCA'S Lindsay Dentlinger is following those developments. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The African Transformation Movement is back in court on Wednesday. ATM wants it to force a secret ballot in a motion of no confidence in President Cyril Ramaphosa. READ:Â ATM to ask Parliament to postpone motion of no confidence in Ramaphosa The party says Ramaphosa failed to disclose to Parliament that he benefitted financially from his ANC presidential campaign in 2017. ATM has taken a jab at National Assembly Speaker Thandi Modise's decision to refuse a secret ballot claiming she's biased and irrational.